   SANTA ANA, Calif. -- Metropolitan Ciruits Inc. said that
General Electric Co. filed a $1.7 million lawsuit against the
company to collect certain debts.
   A General Electric spokesman said the debt for its sale to
Metropolitan Circuits of copper-clad laminate was due more
than a year ago.
</LP>
