<LP>
   PASADENA, Calif. -- Jacobs Engineering Group Inc. said it
received a $25 million contract from a division of Borden
Inc. to build two production facilities in Jackson, Miss.,
and Chatsworth, Calif.
   Jacobs said it will transform an existing structure in
Jackson into a 440,000-square-foot facility for the
manufacture and distribution of products for Borden's grocery
and specialty products division.
</LP>
