<LP>
   The following were among yesterday's offerings and
pricings in U.S. and non-U.S. capital markets, with terms and
syndicate manager, as compiled by Dow Jones Capital Markets
Report.
                                                                                                       

                        CORPORATE
                                                                                                       

</LP>
<TEXT>
   Chemical Waste Management Inc. -- $500 million redemption
amount of liquid yield option notes due Aug. 16, 2010, priced
at $306.56 for each $1,000 note, for a yield to maturity of
6%. The LYONs, as zero-coupon convertible subordinated notes,
are typically priced at a deep discount. The notes are
convertible into common at $26.255 a share, representing an
18% premium over yesterday's closing price. Rated single-A-2
by Moody's Investors Service Inc. and double-A-minus by
Standard &amp; Poor's Corp., the issue will be sold through
underwriters led by Merrill Lynch Capital Markets.
   Merrill Lynch &amp; Co. -- $100 million of 9.25% notes due
Nov. 15, 1994, priced at par. The non-callable notes were
priced at a spread of 93 basis points above the Treasury's
four-year note. Rated single-A-2 by Moody's and single-A by
S&amp;P, the issue will be sold through underwriters led by
Merrill Lynch Capital Markets.
   Navistar Financial Corp. -- $100 million of 9 3/4% notes
due Aug. 15, 1995, priced at 99.80 to yield 9.801%. The
non-callable notes were priced at 145 basis points above the
Treasury's five-year note. Rated Baa-3 by Moody's and
triple-B-minus by S&amp;P, the issue will be sold through
underwriters led by Lehman Brothers.
                                                                                                       

                        MUNICIPAL
                                                                                                       

   Westchester County, N.Y. -- $75 million of improvement
unlimited tax bonds, Series 1990A, due Feb. 1, 1992-2010, via
a Chase Securities Inc. group. The bonds, rated triple-A,
were priced for reoffering to yield from 5.90% in 1992 to
6.95% in 2008-2010. There are no term bonds.
   Monmouth County, N.J. -- $68.7 million of general
improvement bonds Series 1990, due Aug. 1, 1991-2002, and
utility bonds Series 1990, due Aug. 1, 1991-2010, via a
Merrill Lynch Capital Markets group. The $38.2 million
general improvement bonds are priced to yield from 5.80% in
1991 to 6.75% in 2002. The $30.5 million utility bonds are
priced to yield from 5.80% in 1991 to 7.05% in 2009 and 2010.
The bonds are rated double-A-1/double-A. There are no term
bonds.
                                                                                                       

