with a coupon rate of 8.90% at 99 41/64 to yield 9.072%. The
CFC 11-A Grantor Trust, which totals about $139 million, is a
marine receivables-backed certificate issue. The securities
are expected to be rated triple-A by Moody's and S&amp;P based on
the quality of the underlying loans and a 15% Capmac surety
bond. Capmac, or Capital Markets Assurance Corp., is a unit
of Citicorp. The originator and servicer of the underlying
marine loans is Chrysler First Inc. The securities have an
average life of 3.19 years and a stated final maturity of
Aug. 15, 1997. The CFC 11-B Grantor Trust, which totals about
$75 million, is a recreational vehicles-backed certificate
issue. A triple-A rating from Moody's and S&amp;P is expected
based on the quality of the underlying loans and a 13.5%
Capmac surety bond. The originator and servicer of the
underlying RV loans is Chrysler First Inc. The average life
is 3.28 years assuming monthly prepayments at 1% of the
original loan balance. Stated final maturity is Aug. 15,
1997. Both issues were priced at 90 basis points over
three-year Treasury notes.
                                                                                                       

