<HL>
   Business Brief -- Avnet Inc.:
   Fourth-Period Net Fell 62%
   After Restructuring Charge
</HL>
<DATE>
08/10/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   AVT
</CO>
<IN>
EARNINGS (ERN)
SEMICONDUCTORS, INTEGRATED CHIPS (SEM)
</IN>
<LP>
   Avnet Inc., after taking a restructuring charge, reported
fiscal fourth-quarter net income fell 62%.
   The maker of industrial and consumer products said net
income was $7.5 million, or 22 cents a share, after the $9.8
million charge. Year-earlier net was $19.8 million, or 55
cents a share.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Sales for the quarter ended June 30 were $447.9 million,
down from the year-earlier $456.9 million.
   For the fiscal year, the New York firm said net income
rose to $56.5 million, or $1.57 a share, from $54 million, or
$1.51 a share. Sales were $1.75 billion, down from $1.92
billion. Year-ago results included a gain of $1.3 million on
the sale of four operations.
   The company said the restructuring charge includes costs
related to the disposition of its Taiwanese operation and
restructuring of its Avnet Computer Technologies and Harper
S.I.D operations.
   Avnet Chairman Leon Machiz said that, despite the 9%
decline in fiscal-year sales, earnings from operations,
excluding the charge, rose 26%. Net operating margins
increased to 3.8% from 2.7%.
</TEXT>
